    <div class="prose">
      <p>If you're an electrical contractor in 2026, your competitors are already running Meta ads. The question isn't whether Facebook advertising works for electricians — it's whether your ads are outperforming theirs.</p>
      <p>In this guide, we'll walk through exactly how to set up, optimize, and scale Meta ads for your electrical business. Whether you do residential service calls or commercial construction contracts, this playbook applies.</p>

      <h2>Why Meta Ads Work for Electricians</h2>
      <p>Electricians have a natural advantage with Meta advertising: <strong>high-intent, local demand</strong>. When someone needs an emergency rewiring or a panel upgrade, they search and scroll with urgency. Meta's targeting lets you intercept that demand at the right moment.</p>
      <ul>
        <li><strong>Hyper-local targeting:</strong> Serve ads only within your service radius</li>
        <li><strong>Visual proof:</strong> Before/after photos of panel upgrades, rewiring, EV charger installs</li>
        <li><strong>Retargeting:</strong> Follow up with website visitors who didn't book immediately</li>
        <li><strong>Lookalike audiences:</strong> Find more customers like your best ones</li>
      </ul>

      <h2>Step 1: Set Up Your Campaign Structure</h2>
      <p>Use this proven structure for electrical contractors:</p>
      <ul>
        <li><strong>Campaign objective:</strong> Leads (optimized for conversions)</li>
        <li><strong>Ad set budget:</strong> Start at $30–50/day per ad set</li>
        <li><strong>Targeting radius:</strong> 20–40 km around your service area</li>
        <li><strong>Audience:</strong> Homeowners 25–65, interested in home improvement, property maintenance, or construction</li>
      </ul>

      <h2>Step 2: Create Ads That Convert</h2>
      <p>The best-performing ad formats for electricians in 2026:</p>
      <ul>
        <li><strong>Video walkthroughs:</strong> Show a quick breaker panel replacement or EV charger install (60–90 seconds)</li>
        <li><strong>Before/after carousel:</strong> 3–5 cards showing transformation projects</li>
        <li><strong>Customer testimonial video:</strong> A real client talking about their emergency electrical fix</li>
      </ul>

      <h2>Step 3: Optimize Your Landing Page</h2>
      <p>This is where most electricians lose money. Your Facebook ad might be great, but if the landing page doesn't convert, you're burning budget.</p>
      <p><strong>Critical landing page elements:</strong></p>
      <ul>
        <li>Service area prominently displayed</li>
        <li>Click-to-call button (60% of electrician leads come via phone)</li>
        <li>Service list with transparent pricing</li>
        <li>Licensed & insured badges</li>
        <li>Google review widget nearby</li>
      </ul>

      <h2>The Gap Most Electricians Miss</h2>
      <p>Here's what our research across hundreds of electrical contractors revealed: <strong>most are running ads but have no follow-up system.</strong> They capture a lead, call once, leave a voicemail, and never follow up.</p>
      <p>Electricians running ads <em>and</em> an email/SMS follow-up sequence convert at 3x the rate of ad-only electricians. A simple 3-touch sequence — same-day call, next-day email, 3-day follow-up SMS — can double your ROI overnight.</p>

